h4. Problem

When there are multiple updates to the SLA value within the same request, it can result the SLA being overridden.
h4. Cause

The method when we retrieve values vs writing values differ.
{code:java}
issue.getCustomFieldValue(customField);
{code}
 * getCustomFieldValue will load the value, and cache it in a map on the {{IssueImpl}} object.

{code:java}
customField.getCustomFieldType().updateValue(customField, issue, updatingValue);
{code}
 * when we update the value, we write it directly to the database, but do not update this map in the {{IssueImpl}}.

So if in the same request has multiple read/writes, our changes can be overridden as the value retrieved from issue is the original start value (in the map cache), which was not updated with previous writes.
h4. Visible user symptoms/problem

SLA rule sporadically doesn't react (doesn't _pause_, etc) on issue status change.
h4. Workaround:

Missing/Incorrect SLAs can be reconstructed by following the [Missing SLA data in JIRA ServiceDesk|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirakb/missing-sla-data-in-jira-servicedesk-828790603.html] KB.

h3. Summary:
When we created a Custom Field that has its Default Value set and added in a Request Type Form, it would not be shown when trying to get the list of available fields from a Request Type through REST API.
- [JIRA Service Desk Server REST API|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-servicedesk/REST/server/]

h3. Steps to Reproduce:
# Create a Select Custom Field.
# Configure a Default Value for it.
# Add the field to a request type.
# Clarify that the Field is showing when accessing through the Customer Portal.
# Run the following GET REST API below:
{code}/server/#servicedeskapi/servicedesk/{serviceDeskId}/requesttype/{requestTypeId}/field{code}

h3. Expected Result:
A JSON response of:
{code:xml}
{
  "requestTypeFields": [
    {
      "fieldId": "summary",
      "name": "What do you need?",
      "description": "Tell us what you're looking for. For example, 'put me on the mailing list'.",
      "required": true,
      "validValues": [],
      "jiraSchema": {
        "type": "string",
        "system": "summary"
      }
    },
    {
      "fieldId": "description",
      "name": "Why do you need this?",
      "description": "",
      "required": true,
      "validValues": [],
      "jiraSchema": {
        "type": "string",
        "system": "description"
      }
    },
    {
      "fieldId": "customfield_10113",
      "name": "Select Service",
      "description": "",
      "required": false,
      "validValues": [
        {
          "value": "10003",
          "label": "Fix",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "value": "10004",
          "label": "Replace",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "value": "10005",
          "label": "Remove",
          "children": []
        }
      ],
      "jiraSchema": {
        "type": "option",
        "custom": "com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:select",
        "customId": 10113
      }
    },
    {
      "fieldId": "labels",
      "name": "Labels",
      "description": "",
      "required": false,
      "validValues": [],
      "jiraSchema": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": "string",
        "system": "labels"
      }
    },
    {
      "fieldId": "customfield_10002",
      "name": "",
      "description": "",
      "required": false,
      "validValues": [],
      "jiraSchema": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": "sd-customerorganization",
        "custom": "com.atlassian.servicedesk:sd-customer-organizations",
        "customId": 10002
      }
    }
  ],
  "canRaiseOnBehalfOf": true,
  "canAddRequestParticipants": true
}
{code}

h3. Actual Result:
The custom field will be hidden, in this case, it is *Select Service* from above:
{code:xml}
{
  "requestTypeFields": [
    {
      "fieldId": "summary",
      "name": "What do you need?",
      "description": "Tell us what you're looking for. For example, 'put me on the mailing list'.",
      "required": true,
      "validValues": [],
      "jiraSchema": {
        "type": "string",
        "system": "summary"
      }
    },
    {
      "fieldId": "description",
      "name": "Why do you need this?",
      "description": "",
      "required": true,
      "validValues": [],
      "jiraSchema": {
        "type": "string",
        "system": "description"
      }
    },
    {
      "fieldId": "labels",
      "name": "Labels",
      "description": "",
      "required": false,
      "validValues": [],
      "jiraSchema": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": "string",
        "system": "labels"
      }
    },
    {
      "fieldId": "customfield_10002",
      "name": "",
      "description": "",
      "required": false,
      "validValues": [],
      "jiraSchema": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": "sd-customerorganization",
        "custom": "com.atlassian.servicedesk:sd-customer-organizations",
        "customId": 10002
      }
    }
  ],
  "canRaiseOnBehalfOf": true,
  "canAddRequestParticipants": true
}
{code}

h3. Workaround:
- Set the default value back to {{None}}
